title: Portland Timbers-Los Angeles Galaxy: Live updates, score and game chat
text:
The Portland Timbers (13-11-8, 47 points) are kicking off against the Los Angeles Galaxy (14-9-9, 51 points) Sunday at 4 p.m. at StubHub Center.
Live updates will appear in the comments section below around game time.
What: Portland Timbers vs. Los Angeles Galaxy .
When: 4 p.m. Sunday.
TV Channel/Radio/Live Stream : TV FOX Sports 1 (Comcast 408/723) | Radio on 750 The Game | Spanish radio La GranD 1150 AM | Online on FOX Sports Go.
Where : StubHub Center, Carson, California.
At stake: A playoff berth. With two games left in the regular season, the Timbers are sitting just below the red line, tied on point total with the sixth-place San Jose Earthquakes (13-12-8, 47 points). The Timbers have a game in hand on San Jose, but the Earthquakes hold the tiebreaker over the Timbers. The top six teams in each conference make playoffs. The Timbers could go a long way toward ensuring themselves a berth into the playoffs with a result at Los Angeles.
